<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Writing on DEDE</title><link>https://wilfrantz.github.io/tags/writing/</link><description>Recent content in Writing on DEDE</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 08 Aug 2019 14:10:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://wilfrantz.github.io/tags/writing/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Writing a New Post</title><link>https://wilfrantz.github.io/posts/2019-08-08-write-a-new-post/</link><pubDate>Thu, 08 Aug 2019 14:10:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wilfrantz.github.io/posts/2019-08-08-write-a-new-post/</guid><description>&lt;p>This tutorial will guide you how to write a post in the &lt;em>Chirpy&lt;/em> template, and it&amp;rsquo;s worth reading even if you&amp;rsquo;ve used Jekyll before, as many features require specific variables to be set.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="naming-and-path">
 Naming and Path
 &lt;a class="heading-link" href="#naming-and-path">
 &lt;i class="fa-solid fa-link" aria-hidden="true" title="Link to heading">&lt;/i>
 &lt;span class="sr-only">Link to heading&lt;/span>
 &lt;/a>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;h2 id="front-matter">
 Front Matter
 &lt;a class="heading-link" href="#front-matter">
 &lt;i class="fa-solid fa-link" aria-hidden="true" title="Link to heading">&lt;/i>
 &lt;span class="sr-only">Link to heading&lt;/span>
 &lt;/a>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72">---&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#7ee787">title&lt;/span>:&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff">TITLE&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#7ee787">date&lt;/span>:&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff">YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS +/-TTTT&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#7ee787">categories&lt;/span>:&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"> &lt;/span>[&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff">TOP_CATEGORIE, SUB_CATEGORIE]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#7ee787">tags&lt;/span>:&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"> &lt;/span>[&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff">TAG] &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#8b949e;font-style:italic"># TAG names should always be lowercase&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72">---&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#6e7681">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>The posts&amp;rsquo; &lt;em>layout&lt;/em> has been set to &lt;code>post&lt;/code> by default, so there is no need to add the variable &lt;em>layout&lt;/em> in the Front Matter block.
{: .prompt-tip }&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>